definition.value: A member of the class of pentachlorobenzenes that is benzene in which five of the hydrogens are replaced by chlorines. Now classed as a persistent organic pollutant under the Stockholm Convention.
A proanthocyanidin isolated from Dracaena draco.

An organofluorine compound that is haloperidol in which the hydroxy group has been eliminated with the introduction of a double bond in the piperidine ring, and the 4-chlorophenyl group has been replaced by a benzimidazol-2-on-1-yl group. It is used in the management of chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting, and in conjunction with an opioid analgesic such as fentanyl to maintain the patient in a calm state of neuroleptanalgesia with indifference to surroundings but still able to cooperate with the surgeon.
A broad-spectrum, intravenous beta-lactam antibiotic of the carbapenem subgroup.

A member of the class of piperidinylimidazoles that is 1-methyl-4-(1-propylimidazol-2-yl)piperidine carrying additional 3,4-dichlorophenyl and 2-(cyclopropylamino)pyrimidin-4-yl substituents at positions 4 and 5 respectively.
A diadenosyl diphosphate having two 5'-adenosyl residues attached at the P(1)- and P(2)-positions of the diphosphate.
A disaccharide consisting of two 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl units joined via an alpha-(2->4)-linkage.
A bromoalkane that is ethane carrying a bromo substituent. It is an alkylating agent used as a chemical intermediate in various organic syntheses.
N-Ethylpiperidine in which one of the hydrogens attached to the methyl group is substituted by a 4-butoxybenzoyl group.
A bromophenol containing only hydroxy and bromo substituents that are para to one another.
